cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.NE 

This paper proposes a new attention mechanism for convolutional neural networks (CNNs) to fully exploit global correlations. The proposed method is validated on the task of person re-identification, which falls under computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also extensively evaluates the effectiveness of the proposed method, which is a common practice in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the proposed method involves convolutional operations, which are commonly used in multimedia (cs.MM) and neural networks (cs.NE).
